BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:kACjrWsK-eMqMdiBQC3cr
SUMMARY:Cloud Room Coworking Open House Week
DTSTAMP:20260306T013218Z
DTSTART:20260306T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Curious about coworking and looking for the perfect spot to get
	 work done and reach your goals? Join us for a complimentary day during Op
	en House Week and experience what it’s like to be a part of our incredible
	 community!\n\nWhat's Included:\n\nFree Trial Day: Pick any day during Ope
	n House Week to try out our coworking space\, free of charge! Arrive anyti
	me 9am or later — whatever works best with your schedule.\n\nAccess to our
	 beautiful workspace including quiet desk space with monitors\, large loun
	ge area\, phone booths\, bar\, and outdoor patio.\n\nComplimentary coffee\
	, tea\, snacks and kombucha.\n\nHigh-speed Wi-Fi\, printing\, and meeting 
	rooms available for rent\n\nThe chance to meet like-minded professionals a
	nd get a feel for the Cloud Room vibe.\n\nSpecial Offer:\n\nIf you love yo
	ur free day with us and decide to become a member\, we’ll waive your initi
	ation fees when you sign up!\n\nHow to Join:\n\nReserve your free trial da
	y by selecting one day of your choice on our Calendly \\(one free trial da
	y per person\\)\n\nShow up and enjoy your day at Cloud Room! Be sure to ch
	eck in with the staff at the front of the lounge so we can give you a quic
	k tour of the space and get you set up with the wifi.\n\nSign up for membe
	rship to take advantage of waived initiation fees.\n\nDon’t miss this chan
	ce to test out our space\, meet amazing people\, and see if Cloud Room is 
	the perfect fit for your work needs!\n\nSpaces are limited—RSVP today.\n\n
	https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/cloud-room-coworking-open-ho
	use-week/18050488/2026-03-06T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/cloud-room-coworking-open
	-house-week/18050488/2026-03-06T00
LOCATION:The Cloud Room\, 1424 11th Ave Suite 400\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT8H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Hyb0Z9sP6Z3TXep29rdeI
SUMMARY:DIY Wire Cloches Level 1
DTSTAMP:20260306T013218Z
DTSTART:20260306T173000Z
DESCRIPTION:Taught in partnership with Northwest Perennial Alliance. In thi
	s hands-on workshop learn how to make the wire cloches NPA uses in the Per
	ennial Border at Bellevue Botanical Garden to keep rabbits from eating the
	 plants. They make great plant supports too! Once you learn wiring skills\
	, you can make them any size and style that suits you\, creating something
	 worthy of a place in your garden. We will supply everything you need to m
	ake one medium-sized cloche and you will receive a materials list with inf
	ormation on suppliers and tools. $24.50 BBGS or NPA Member/$35 Non-Member\
	n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/diy-wire-cloches-level-1/
	17923220/2026-03-06T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/diy-wire-cloches-level-1/
	17923220/2026-03-06T00
LOCATION:Bellevue Botanical Garden\, 12001 Main St\, Bellevue\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:TDXgrcUc0u2xzVQXweCgI
SUMMARY:DIY Wire Cloches Level 2
DTSTAMP:20260306T013218Z
DTSTART:20260306T200000Z
DESCRIPTION:Taught in partnership with Northwest Perennial Alliance. In thi
	s hands-on workshop you will take your cloche making to the next level. Us
	ing skills learned from the Level 1 class you will have the opportunity to
	 create a taller cloche or two medium size cloches. Learn to stylize your 
	garden cloches so they add interest as well as functionality to your home 
	garden. We will supply the wire and clips. You will receive a materials li
	st with information on suppliers and tools. Some experience is recommended
	. $35 BBGS & NPA Members/$50 Non-Member.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/e
	vents/#/details/diy-wire-cloches-level-2/17923221/2026-03-06T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/diy-wire-cloches-level-2/
	17923221/2026-03-06T00
LOCATION:Bellevue Botanical Garden\, 12001 Main St\, Bellevue\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
